<br><table width='95%' align='center' border='0' cellspacing='1' cellpadding='0' bgcolor='#345487'><tr><td>
<table width='100%' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='3' class='maintitle'><tr><td class='maintitle'><img src='../forums/style_images/1/nav_m.gif' border='0'  alt='' width='8' height='8'></td>
<td width='100%' class='maintitle'>Why donate? - Because you should!</td>
</tr></table></td></tr><tr><td class='mainbg'><table width='100%' border='0' cellspacing='1' cellpadding='4'>
<tr><td class='forum2' width='59%'>Topics covered here:<BR>
<b><a href="#why">1. Why donate?</a><br>
<a href="#where">2. Where do the donations go?</a><br>
<a href="#do">3. Do I have to donate?</a><br>
<a href="#get">4. What do I get for donating?</a></B><br>
<p><H2 id=why>1. Why donate?</H2>Donations are recorded as a &#8220;donation level&#8221; against your user 
  account. Various downloads&#8217; and areas within the site require you to be 
  above this level in order to be accessible. This site is entirely funded and 
  run on a voluntary basis. No corporate finding or sponsorship is currently used 
  to progress any of the content within, any aspects that are associated with 
  a particular company or organisation will be clearly marked as such. This allows 
  for a completely unbiased and balanced approach to be taken when putting various 
  views across and increases your access to cost effective but high quality solutions.<br><br>
<H2 id=where>2. Where do the donations go? </H2>Donations, fundamentally, are distributed entirely at my discretion, however, 
  I have set myself clear guidelines for the use of these funds.<br>
  The primary uses, will be to &#8220;buy&#8221; mine, and others time for future 
  developments, along with providing more reliable and new services, such as a 
  servers, leagues, competitions, and other things to increase the enjoyment of 
  your stay here.<br>
  Other than this, I intend to redistribute some of the funding to other related 
  sites enabling them also to grow, and improve their services. The current plan 
  is to have donations 'expire' 1 year after the initial contribution is made, 
  beta testers, certified developers and free4life members will not be subject 
  to donations expiring.<br><br>
  <H2 id=do>3. Do I have to donate? </H2>Whilst donation of funds is preferred, I accept that a significant number 
  of people have contributed time and energy into this project or related projects. 
  This will count as a donation other than money. If you believe you fit into 
  this category <a href="http://www.cam-direct.co.uk/forums/index.php?act=Mail&CODE=00&MID=1">please 
  provide a brief description</a> of the work you have done, with any relevant 
  information. Please note in this case your user name should be the same and 
  any disputes will be settled via an adjudication process.<br>
  <br>
  <H2 id=get>4. What do I get for donating? </H2>Access to various areas and downloads within the site, these include:<br>
  &#8226; Full installers for applications and games.<br>
  &#8226; New - even better- &#8220;tech demo&#8221; releases demonstrating new 
  technologies or developments.<br>
  &#8226; Additional routes, mission-scripts and other add-ons which build upon 
  the open releases available to all.<br>
  &#8226; Various developer resources, (most developers should see 3.)</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class='mainfoot' colspan='5'>&nbsp;</td></tr> </table></td></tr></table><BR>
</td>
